  {
    "client_msg_id": "7a951dcb-e91a-4c4a-8e92-4d3095682232",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Why would you want to represent numbers / booleans as strings? Apart from the round trip of \"Number represented as string which is represented as a list of numbers\" that doesn't seem right, this would also require parsing every time you'd want to do anything useful with numbers / bools. I don't see how this could make a theory easier either, could you elaborate on this? Thanks in advance :wink:",
    "user": "UAL7940NM",
    "ts": "1542788627.262600",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
