  {
    "client_msg_id": "f8d5ca57-a942-4ae0-ae18-dc6c5ecfded8",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Well there's pros and cons. In the world of possible things you can write to represent values, bools and numbers are only two value types in a much wider range of values, all of which we probably fall back onto strings to represent. By starting with strings you generalise to \"it is what it looks like\" - if it parses as a number, it's a number, and you can now define a universe of possible regexps to declare in fine grain any other type of value. By reducing to the simple \"type = syntax\", it could make the logic you're looking for easier in some way. Or maybe not. Dunno what you're looking for really!! :smile:",
    "user": "UE6EFEPTQ",
    "ts": "1542791327.262800",
